{
  "texts": [
    "Further, AI systems can be multiplied quickly.",
    "In the current paradigm, training cutting edge AI models requires a lot more compute than running a few models.",
    "For this reason, when there is enough compute available to train a PAI, there will likely also be enough compute to run hundreds of thousands or millions of copies of it (Davidson 2023; Steinhardt 2023).",
    "With further availability of compute, the number of AI system can rapidly increase from there.",
    "To summarize, we should expect that PAI systems would not only have cognitive advantages in some domains to humans, but process information much faster, function tirelessly, coordinate seamlessly and multiply quickly."
  ]
}